Ugandan medical officials have prevented Kenyan truck drivers from crossing into Uganda unless they take mandatory Covid-19 tests, but the drivers have refused to take the tests.
Truck drivers have been complaining of massive queues at Uganda's eastern border as officials carry out mandatory coronavirus testing. In the western district of Hoima, ironically the area where Uganda discovered large oil deposits earlier this century, a liter of fuel was selling at $3.40 Â up from $1.13 previously. The pumps had run dry at other petrol stations in the north and west of the landlocked East African country --ChannelAfrica--